    "headline": "3 Consumer Stocks We Find Risky",
    "summary": "The performance of consumer discretionary businesses is closely linked to economic cycles. This sensitive demand profile can cause discretionary stocks to plummet when macro uncertainty enters the fray, and over the past six months, the industry has shed 8.5%. This drawdown was worse than the S&P 500’s 1.9% fall.",
